
what .js lang can do on HTML-page in browser-envi?

   .js-lang with browser/web APIs, can bring any dynamic functionality to web-page.

    browser/web APIs ==> functionality implemented and abstracted 
                         as js-objs by browsers based on w3c standards.

    e.g  DOM , XHR , Timer , Etc....
    
    using DOM

   --> can create/retreive/update/delete HTML elements.
   --> can change element's attributes 
   --> can change element's styles
   --> can change element's inner-content
   --> can validate form-fields before submit
   --> can create rich UI components ( e.f layouts , datepickers , etc...)
   --> can listen for events ( user / broswer events)

   using XHR 

   --> can communicate with server async and update results in existing page

   using Timer API

   --> setTimeout,setInterval 

   HTML-5 APIs

   --> canvas : drawing element ( can draw any shapes/text)
   --> audio/videp : multimedia support
   --> storage API
   --> webworker
   --> SSE
   --> websockets
   --> geo

   --> etc...


   reference : caniuse.com


---------------------------------------------------------------------


 limitations/complexities of plain-js ( script written by you)

  --> browser compatibility
  --> too much code for simple actions
  --> performance ( i.e DOM selection,manipulation, etc...)
  --> memory management ( i.e cleaning un-used eleemnts/objects , unbind event listeners)

  --> code oraganization is difficult.
  --> data-binding support 


  solns 

  --> using JS libraries and F.Ws


JS libraries:

 --> jQuery 


     limitations of jQuery

     --> close to DOM. ( when view change , we need to change js-code)
     --> data-binding is manual.
     --> very difficult for large-scale appln dev.


     solns:

     using Frameworks ( complete structure for js-appln dev)


     1. Angular 1.x --> google team

     2. Angular 2.x 

     3. React --> facebook

     4. backbone

     5. EXTJS ( commercial )

     6...........

